    "notes": "Ⓟ 1995, 1997, 1998 The Decca Record Company Limited, London.\nⒸ 1998 The Decca Record Company Limited, London, a Polygram company.\nCD's are made in Germany. Printed in Germany. Total time: 128:38. CD1: 65:43 and CD2: 62:55\nCover jewel case: Kirckman harpsichord; photo courtesy of Steven Devine at Finchcocks.\nCover booklet: Portrait of J.S. Bach by Elias Gottlob Haussmann - Museum für Geschichte der Stadt, Leipzig.\nThe Academy of Ancient Music on authentic instruments. Pitch: a' = 415 Hz.\nThis recording was monitored on B&W loudspeakers.\n\nRecording locations:\n- EMI Abbey Road, Studio 1, 5-7 August 1993 (BWV 1055, 1058);\n- Henry Wood Hall, London, 12-14 August 1994 (BWV 1053, 1054, 1056);\n- Henry Wood Hall, London, 2-3 February 1995 (BWV 1044, 1052, 1057);\n\nThe 36-page glossy booklet contains a track and credits-list as well as notes in English, French and German.\nThe booklet and 2 CD's are sheltered by a (fat) chubby double jewel case with black trays.",
